CORE GAMEPLAY LOOP

Children:

1. Enter page
2. Receive Pokémon checklist
3. Search for hidden Pokémon
4. Discover bonus secrets
5. Revisit pages repeatedly
6. Unlock hidden lore/connections
7. Compare pages with friends

The goal is “discovery density.”

Every revisit reveals something new.

⸻

VISUAL STYLE SYSTEM

A major differentiator:

Each page can shift artistic style.

Examples:

* Classic Sugimori-inspired watercolor
* Vintage Game Boy palette
* Trading-card holo style
* Anime splash style
* Storybook ink style
* Hand-drawn sketchbook style
* Retro manga style

This keeps the book visually fresh and collectible.

⸻

CARD INTEGRATION SYSTEM

One of the strongest expansion opportunities:

Hidden Pokémon can become collectible cards later.

Example:
A hidden Lapras from Cerulean City becomes:
“Cerulean Harbor Lapras”

The exact same pose/background from the book becomes:

* Promo card
* Sticker
* Poster
* Holo card
* Mini print
* Digital collectible

This creates:

* continuity
* emotional attachment
* collectible identity

Children remember:
“I FOUND THIS ONE!”

